params._defaultGrave: The grave address to pass to the deployed proxies
params._defaultGuard: The guard address to pass to the deployed proxies
params._defaultTarget: The target address to pass to the deployed proxies
params._factory: The address of the contract factory to "wrap"

deployProxy(bytes32,uint256,address[]).details: Calls `deploy` on the contract factory, then atomically calls `setup` on the deployed proxy

params._salt: The create2 salt for the contract factory
params._signers: The initial signers for the multisig (proxy)
params._threshold: The signer threshold for the multisig (proxy)

deployProxy(bytes32,uint256,address[]).return: The address of the deployed proxy

isAuthorized(address,bytes4).details: The check performed by calling `canCall` on the Guard instance. If no Guard instance is configured, function returns false (as a failsafe).

params._sig: The function selector of the function being called.

isAuthorized(address,bytes4).return: True, if the caller is authorized to make the call.

params._guard: The address of the new Guard instance.

isAuthorized(address,bytes4).notice: isAuthorized will return `true` if `_src` address can call the function with the `_sig` function selector in the current context (in this contract).

setGuard(address).notice: setGuard will set the new Guard instance. The caller must have permissions to call this function in the current Guard instance.

userdoc.notice: A wrapper contract for atomically deploying and intializing delegatecall proxies. Tightly coupled with both Proxy.sol and Multisig.sol
